parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission failure can cause the vehicle to lose power or stall, leading to a loss of control, which can increase the risk of accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle fails to accelerate as needed
the transmission slips into neutral
unusual sounds or noises are heard while driving
the vehicle stalls or loses power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The uncommanded stalling of the vehicle can cause a sudden loss of power, increasing the risk of accidents, especially when driving at high speeds or in heavy traffic.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls unexpectedly
often after filling up with gas
while sitting still or driving at highway speeds
and may be accompanied by unknown warning lights.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the dealer to diagnose and repair the issue can lead to prolonged periods of vehicle downtime, leaving the owner without a safe and reliable vehicle.
symptoms: The dealer is unable to determine the cause of the failure
and the vehicle is not repaired
despite multiple visits and complaints from the owner.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the headlight to illuminate properly can significantly reduce visibility, increasing the risk of accidents, especially at night.
symptoms: The headlight fails to illuminate properly
reducing visibility to less than 30 feet ahead of the vehicle
making it difficult to see road markings.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unexpected closure of the power lift tailgate can cause injury to individuals nearby, and potentially lead to accidents or damage to the vehicle.
symptoms: The power lift tailgate closes unexpectedly
hitting individuals nearby
causing injury.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Faulty Wheel Speed Sensor Causing ABS Issues and Vehicle Stalls
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A faulty wheel speed sensor can cause the Anti-lock Braking System (ABS) to malfunction, leading to vehicle stalls, which can increase the risk of accidents, especially when driving at high speeds.
symptoms: The ABS light is illuminated on the dashboard
the vehicle stalls while driving
multiple instrument cluster lights are illuminated
the vehicle experiences repeated stalls
the dealership is unable to repair the issue despite multiple attempts.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unavailability of repair parts can lead to extended downtime for the vehicle, causing inconvenience to the owner and potentially affecting their daily life or business.
symptoms: The dealership is unable to provide an estimated time of arrival (ETA) for the required repair parts
the vehicle is in the repair shop for an extended period
the owner is unable to use their vehicle for an extended period.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unintended activation of the Automatic Emergency Braking (AEB) system can cause sudden and unexpected stops, which can lead to accidents, injuries, or even fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle suddenly stops or brakes without warning
the AEB lights flash
the brakes lock up without any obstruction or reason
the system is overly sensitive and triggers false alarms
the system activates when there is no apparent danger.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: An overly sensitive ADAS can cause unnecessary and potentially hazardous interventions, leading to driver confusion, loss of control, or accidents.
symptoms: The system frequently triggers false alarms
the system is overly reactive to minor obstacles or parked vehicles
the system causes unnecessary braking or steering interventions
the system is prone to errors or misjudgments.
